/*S*/ Introduction
/*S*/ Einleitung-Node
@node "Introduction" "CAFIC - Introduction"
@{b}@{u}1. Introduction@{uu}@{ub}
@{i}To avoid useless reading this documentation, it  is  mentioned  that  CAFIC
runs only on AMIGA-Computers with OS 2.0 or better.
CAFIC is a program,  which uses the Intuition-Add-On @{"MUI" LINK "mui.copyright"} by Stefan  Stuntz.
So MUI (at least version 3.x is required.)@{ui}

@{"Disclaimer" LINK "disclaim"}
@{"Lawful" LINK "copyright"}

@{b}What is CAFIC?@{ub}

CAFIC is a program, which shall makes it easier to create FreshIcons.

CAFIC stands for @{b}C@{ub}omputer @{b}A@{ub}ided @{b}F@{ub}resh @{b}I@{ub}con @{b}C@{ub}reating
(This name is not to be seen serious)

From a picture you cut 2 blocks with the mouse. The 1st is unselected image
of the new icon, the other the selected image. After cutting you just click
"Save" and right after that you got your brand new fascinating FreshIcon.

Of course, it's possible to set the type of icon you want to create.

Last change of CAFIC: 8. Januar 1997
@endnode
