/*E*/
/*S*/ Startdescription
/*S*/ common
@node "Startdescription" "2. CAFIC - Startdescription"
@{b}@{u}2. Startdescription@{uu}@{ub}
CAFIC can be started either from your Shell or from your Workbench.

@{"The start from Shell" LINK "shellstart"}
@{"The start from Workbench" LINK "wbstart"}

After the start, CAFIC opens its GUI.
@endnode
/*E*/
/*S*/ Shellstart
@NODE "shellstart" "2.1 CAFIC - Startdescription/Shellstart"
@{u}2.1 The Shellstart@{uu}

When you run CAFIC from your Shell, you can use the following parameters:

@{b}?@{ub}
Prints the parametertemplate:
    SM=SCREENMODEID/K,LANGUAGE/K,PIC=PICTURE,SAVENAME:


@{b}SM@{ub} or @{b}SCREENMODEID@{ub}
To force CAFIC to use a special screenmode for the pictures  out  of  which
you  want  to  cut  your  new icons, you can use this argument. Specify the
ID-Number of the screenmode after the keyword either in decimal or hex with
leading @{b}0x@{ub}.  If you are not familiar with these numbers, use 0 or don't use
this keyword.

An Example:
    Start CAFIC with forcing the MULTISCAN-Productivity-Mode:

    1.Workbench:> CAFIC SM=0x39024


@{b}LANGUAGE@{ub}
Forces CAFIC to use a given language for the GUI. If you don't specify this
parameter  or  you use a language for which the catalog-file doesn't exist,
the language you set up in the locale-preferences will be  tried.  If  this
fails too, the build-in english language comes to action.

An Example:
    Run CAFIC with english GUI:

    5.Workbench:> CAFIC LANGUAGE=english


@{b}PIC@{ub} or @{b}PICTURE@{ub}
With that parameter  you  are  able  to  load  a  source-picture  right  at
start-time.  If you specify a path onle, so a filerequester will be opened,
wanting you for choosing a picture-file  This  is  useful  if  you  have  a
special FreshIcons-develope-directory and work with CAFIC more frequently.

Two Examples:
a)  Run CAFIC and read "Work:Bilder/Icons/ToolIcons.iff" immediately:

    8. Workbench:> CAFIC PIC=Work:Bilder/Icons/ToolIcons.iff

b)  Run CAFIC and choose a pic in the "Bilder:Icons" directory immediately:

    9. Workbench:> CAFIC PICTURE=Bilder:Icons


@{b}SAVENAME@{ub}
Pre-Setting the Base-Name to use when saving the icons.
An Example:

    0. Workbench:> CAFIC SAVENAME=RAM:icon.

The shellparameters can, of course, be used together.
@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*S*/ WBStart
@NODE "wbstart" "2.2. CAFIC - Startdescription/Workbenchstart"
@{u}2.2 The Workbenchstart@{uu}

If you start CAFIC from Workbench, you can tell CAFIC the name of the  file
to  be  loaded  at  start-up  time. To do this click the program-icon once,
press and hold the  shift-key  and  double-click  the  picture-file  to  be
loaded.  Now  CAFIC gets started and the file will be loaded. Remember that
only the first additional selected file will be investigated. If  the  icon
you  selected  belongs  to  a  directory  then  after  opening  the  GUI  a
filerequester will be made up to request the name  of  the  file  you  want
CAFIC to load.

Also tooltypes are supported. Tooltypes are informations,  carried  in  the
several  icons  of  tools,  drawers and projects. These informations can be
edited  with   selectin   the   wanted   icon   once   and   choosing   the
workbench-menuitem icon/information.

CAFIC knows the following Tooltypes:

@{b}SCREENMODEID@{ub}
@{b}SM@{ub} or @{b}SCREENMODEID@{ub}
To force CAFIC to use a special screenmode for the pictures  out  of  which
you  want  to  cut  your  new icons, you can use this argument. Specify the
ID-Number of the screenmode after the keyword either in decimal or hex with
leading @{b}0x@{ub}.  If you are not familiar with these numbers, use 0 or don't use
this keyword.

An Example:
    Force CAFIC to use the MULTISCAN-Productivity-Mode:

        SCREENMODEID=0x39024


@{b}LANGUAGE@{ub}
Forces CAFIC to use a given language for the GUI. If you don't specify this
parameter  or  you use a language for which the catalog-file doesn't exist,
the language you set up in the locale-preferences will be  tried.  If  this
fails too, the build-in english language comes to action.

An Example:
    Run CAFIC with english GUI:

        LANGUAGE=english


@{b}PICTURE@{ub}
With that parameter  you  are  able  to  load  a  source-picture  right  at
start-time.  If you specify a path onle, so a filerequester will be opened,
wanting you for choosing a picture-file  This  is  useful  if  you  have  a
special FreshIcons-develope-directory and work with CAFIC more frequently.

Two Examples:
a)  Run CAFIC and read "Work:Bilder/Icons/ToolIcons.iff" immediately:

        PICTURE=Work:Bilder/Icons/ToolIcons.iff

b)  Run CAFIC and choose a pic in the "Bilder:Icons" directory immediately:

        PICTURE=Bilder:Icons


@{b}SAVENAME@{ub}
Pre-Setting the Base-Name to use when saving the icons.
An Example:

        SAVENAME=RAM:icon.


@ENDNODE
/*E*/
/*E*/
/*S*/ Features
@node "Features" "CAFIC - Features"
@{b}@{u}3. Features@{uu}@{ub}
@{i}Here the features of CAFIC shall be named  and  common  problems  shall  be
told.@{ui}

CAFIC is a Commodity and can therefore be displayed and  managed  with  the
Exchange-tool.

When a picture is displayed by  CAFIC,  CAFIC  tries  to  find  a  matching
screenmode  when  none  is carried in the file. If you don't like this, you
can tell CAFIC at startup-time which screenmode-id to use.

CAFIC recognizes IFF-ILBM-pictures only.

CAFIC supports the bubble-help of MUI.  Move  your  mousepointer  over  the
element  you  want  help  for  and  wait  a  bit  (a  few  seconds). To use
bubble-help, MUI-3.x or better is required.

CAFIC  V1.12:
· was  compiled with SAS/C  V6.56,
· needs MUI 3.x
· supports the locale.library,
· supports multiselect
· supports tooltypes
· supports shellparameters
· has NO ARexxPort.
· perhaps runs on CyberGfx-gfx-boards.

@endnode
/*E*/
/*S*/ Usage
@node "Usage" "CAFIC - Usage"
@{b}@{u}4. Usage@{uu}@{ub}

@{i}What follows is an explanation how to use CAFIC if its GUI is opened.@{ui}

The window contains 11 gadgets, which can be divided in file-, parameter-
and controlgadges.

@{u}The 3 File-Gadgets:@{uu}
· Sourcepicture     - Here you can specify a file to be loaded into CAFIC.
                      This file is a iff-ilbm-picture. Out of them you cut
                      the images for the icons you want to create. It's
                      also possible to drop the icon of the file on this
                      string-gadget. If you drop a directory-icon, a file-
                      requester will be opened showing the contents of the
                      corresponding drawer.

· Savebasename      - With that item you can set up the drawer and the name
                      of the icon to be created. A number-extension will be
                      appended to this basename (see savenumber). As above
                      you can also drop an icon here. If it's a file-icon
                      this name will be taken as the basename, otherwise
                      (if it's an directory-icon) a file-requester will be
                      opened and you can enter the final basename.

· Savenumber        - This number will be appended to the basename before
                      the icon gets saved (without additional chars).
                      After saving the icon, this number will be incremen-
                      ted. So you don't have to give a new name after each
                      saving to avoid overwriting the last saved icon.

@{u}The 3 parameter-gadgets:@{uu}
· Icon-Type         - Here you set up the type of icon to be created with
                      CAFIC.

· Icon-Size         - With that you can tell CAFIC which icon-size to use
                      when cutting the images. You can choose between the
                      default size of the FreshIcons (58 x 38 pixels) or
                      the default size of the FreshDockBrushes or a user-
                      defined size. The last option enables you to create
                      icons of any size you want. This size is defined when
                      you do the first cut. Start- and Stoppoint of a rect-
                      angle you draw with the mouse will determine the size.

· Copyrighttooltype - This tooltype is saved automatically when saving the
                      icon and is used as copyright-tag.

@{u}The 5 control-gadgets:@{uu}
· Cut               - Starts the cutting of the icons.

· Test              - Opens a little window for testing the cut icons.

· Save              - Saves the icon.

· Info              - A click on this gadget opens a next window containing
                      informations about CAFIC.

· Quit              - To quit CAFIC, press this gadget.
@endnode
